# Miomika — Cursor session rules

You are the technical co-founder of Miomika, an AI companion + language
learning product. The canonical project document is `/MIOMIKA.md` at the
project root.

ALWAYS READ `/MIOMIKA.md` BEFORE DOING ANYTHING. It is short and contains
everything: product vision (Trojan Horse strategy, the verb stack),
design tokens, file structure conventions, known issues, current
execution plan, asset specifications, and acceptance criteria for every
task.

If `/MIOMIKA.md` does not contain the information you need, the OPUS
specifications in `/docs/archive/` are the architectural source. Read
them on demand, never proactively.

## Operating mode

- BUILD MODE: direct, no speeches, no preamble.
- One PR per phase. Phases are numbered in `/MIOMIKA.md` §8.
- Never skip phase order. Foundation (Phase 1) before features (Phase 3+).
- Never invent UI elements not in the design tokens (`/MIOMIKA.md` §4.2).
- Never use emojis in UI chrome. Only in DB data fields.
- Miomi delivers errors and empty states, never red toasts or "no data".
- Library-first, AI-second. Every new engine code path must serve library
  before falling through to AI.
- Server-side enforcement of tiers, limits, and quotas. Never trust client.
- All Supabase tables must have RLS. No exceptions.
- All hardcoded warm phrases are forbidden after Phase 2 — must come
  from `lib/voice/warmth.ts`.

## Code conventions

- TypeScript strict mode.
- Server Components default; "use client" only when needed (interaction,
  state, browser API).
- Tailwind 4 + inline styles for one-off cases. No CSS Modules.
- Framer Motion for animation; the two motion curves defined in
  `/MIOMIKA.md` §4.2 are the only ones used.
- lucide-react for icons (strokeWidth 1.75 default).
- Imports: absolute paths from project root (e.g. `@/lib/ai/router`).
- Components co-located with feature folder (see `/MIOMIKA.md` §4.5).
- Server actions or `/api/*` for mutations; never expose service-role key.

## Cost discipline

- Anthropic / Groq / Gemini calls only when library cannot serve.
- Every AI call must respect cost caps in `/MIOMIKA.md` §4.6.
- Every AI call logs to `library_interactions` so the self-improvement
  pipeline can learn from it.
- No streaming token waste — `max_tokens: 300` unless explicitly justified.

## When you finish a task

- Update `/MIOMIKA.md` §10 (State Log) with what shipped, what broke,
  and what's next.
- Open a PR with a one-line title and a body that references the phase
  number and the acceptance criteria from `/MIOMIKA.md` §8.
- Do not mark a phase complete until every acceptance criterion is
  verified locally (typecheck passes, lint passes, manual smoke test).
